# Codex Writer Findings — PublicMenu Chain: publicmenu-260323-223605-98ba
## Findings
1. [P2] Discounted menu prices still lose fractional precision - `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx:103` and `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx:283` wrap the discounted amount in `Math.round(...)` before `formatPrice`, so any non-zero fractional part is collapsed before rendering. This directly violates Fix 1's "no `Math.round`" rule and still breaks prices that should keep decimals. FIX: remove `Math.round` from both discounted-price paths and pass the computed decimal value directly into the shared formatter, stripping only insignificant trailing zeros.
2. [P3] List-mode stepper is still rendered in the text column instead of over the image - `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx:124-145` renders the `-N+` block below the text when `inCart`, while `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx:148-186` only overlays the standalone `+` button on the image for the not-in-cart state. This preserves the current bug where in-cart list cards grow taller and lose uniform row height. FIX: move the in-cart stepper into the image container as an absolute bottom-right overlay, matching the existing tile-card overlay pattern.
3. [P3] Cart drawer chevron is still too small and does not meet the required tap target - `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:427-429` renders a bare `ChevronDown` with `w-7 h-7` (28px) and no 44x44 clickable wrapper. Fix 3 explicitly requires a 36px icon and a minimum 44x44 touch area. FIX: wrap the chevron in a button with at least `min-w-[44px] min-h-[44px]` or `w-11 h-11`, and increase the icon to `w-9 h-9` or `size={36}`.
4. [P3] Drag handle and close chevron are still split across different layers, so vertical alignment is not solved - `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx:3419-3423` keeps the drawer's default handle at the `DrawerContent` level, while `pages/PublicMenu/CartView.jsx:426-430` renders the chevron inside a separate sticky content row. Because they do not share one wrapper, they cannot be aligned onto the same visual baseline, and the `x.jsx` side of Fix 3 is effectively still open. FIX: render the drag handle and chevron inside one shared top row with `flex items-center`, or hide the default handle and recreate both controls together in the same wrapper.

## Summary
Total: 4 findings (0 P0, 0 P1, 1 P2, 3 P3)

## Prompt Clarity (MANDATORY — do NOT skip this section)
- Overall clarity: 3
- Ambiguous Fix descriptions (list Fix # and what was unclear): Fix 1 points to a `formatPrice` function inside `pages/PublicMenu/MenuView.jsx`, but that file only receives `formatPrice` as a prop and does not define the formatter. Fix 3 says to check `pages/PublicMenu/x.jsx` for `ChevronDown`, but the current file only owns the drawer container/default handle and does not render a chevron.
- Missing context (what info would have helped): The actual shared formatter implementation used by `MenuView` is not included in the allowed page-folder file set, so end-to-end validation of non-discount price formatting is partially blocked within the stated scope.
- Scope questions (anything you weren't sure if it's in scope): Whether Fix 1 should be reviewed only against `MenuView.jsx`'s local price math or against the external shared formatter that `MenuView` receives via props; whether Fix 3 expects the default Vaul handle in `x.jsx` to be treated as part of the fix even though `x.jsx` does not currently render `ChevronDown`.
